{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_58","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/geometry_preview.md | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Geometry Preview Workflow\n     2\t\n     3\tMilestone 5 preview generation is intentionally offline. The preview step reads\n     4\tonly local files that were already produced by the pipeline:\n     5\t\n     6\t- raw mesh: `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`\n     7\t- simplified mesh: `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`\n     8\t- optional skeleton: `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`\n     9\t- surface graph: `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`\n    10\t- patch graph: `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`\n    11\t- optional sidecars: descriptor and QA JSON written by `scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py`\n    12\t\n    13\t## Generate a preview\n    14\t\n    15\tPreview one or more specific root IDs:\n    16\t\n    17\t```bash\n    18\tpython scripts/05_preview_geometry.py --config config/local.yaml --root-id 101 --root-id 102\n    19\t```\n    20\t\n    21\tPreview the active selected subset from `config.paths.selected_root_ids`:\n    22\t\n    23\t```bash\n    24\tpython scripts/05_preview_geometry.py --config config/local.yaml --limit 4\n    25\t```\n    26\t\n    27\tEquivalent Make target:\n    28\t\n    29\t```bash\n    30\tmake preview CONFIG=config/local.yaml\n    31\t```\n    32\t\n    33\tThe output location is deterministic for the exact root-id set. By default the\n    34\tscript writes to:\n    35\t\n    36\t```text\n    37\tconfig.paths.geometry_preview_dir/root-ids-<sorted-root-ids>/\n    38\t```\n    39\t\n    40\tExample:\n    41\t\n    42\t```text\n    43\tdata/processed/previews/root-ids-101-102/index.html\n    44\tdata/processed/previews/root-ids-101-102/summary.json\n    45\tdata/processed/previews/root-ids-101-102/root_ids.txt\n    46\t```\n    47\t\n    48\tThat makes the report path stable enough to reference from run logs, ticket\n    49\tnotes, or review comments.\n    50\t\n    51\t## What the report shows\n    52\t\n    53\tEach root section keeps the following in one place:\n    54\t\n    55\t- raw mesh wireframe\n    56\t- simplified mesh wireframe\n    57\t- skeleton projection or an explicit unavailable marker\n    58\t- surface graph projection\n    59\t- patch graph projection\n    60\t- bundle summary metrics, artifact paths, and QA highlights\n    61\t\n    62\tThe HTML is fully static and does not require a notebook server, Neuroglancer,\n    63\tor FlyWire access.\n    64\t\n    65\t## Reviewer checklist\n    66\t\n    67\tReviewers should look for:\n    68\t\n    69\t- raw vs simplified mesh silhouette staying broadly consistent rather than collapsing or drifting\n    70\t- skeleton presence matching expectations for that neuron and following the same gross orientation as the meshes when available\n    71\t- surface graph coverage matching the simplified geometry instead of showing obvious holes or disconnected clutter\n    72\t- patch graph being non-empty and spatially distributed rather than collapsing to one dominant patch unless that is expected\n    73\t- QA warnings or failures that suggest simplification drift, patch coverage gaps, or coarse graph degeneracy\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
